data.title: New Rainbow Six Siege details from Scott Mitchell
data.description: In this interview, Scott Mitchell talks to us about what to expect from the latest incarnation of the venerable Rainbow Six franchise.

data.title: Interview: Dennis "Svenskeren" Johnsen on life as a pro League of Legends player
data.description: In this interview from a recent visit to Logitech Gaming HQ, SoloMid Jungler Dennis "Svenskeren" Johnsen takes us through a day in the life of a pro gamer, and how companies like Logitech have contributed to the growth of e-sports.

data.title: Interview: Yiliang "Doublelift" Peng on Heroes of the Storm and the issue of player mistreatment
data.description: In this interview from a recent visit to Logitech Gaming HQ, Yiliang "Doublelift" Peng from Team SoloMid talks about his introduction to competitive gaming and how the scene has changed over the years.

data.title: Close-up with the Logitech G410 gaming keyboard
data.description: In this interview, Brent Barry from Logitech gives us a close-up look at the Logitech G410 Atlas Spectrum gaming keyboard.

data.title: Blue Lola Headphones: Flash Review
data.tags: blue lola, blue audio, blue microphones,
data.description: We offer our early impressions of the new Lola headphones from Blue, a lighter follow-up to Blue's Mo-Fi. Overall, the Blue Lola headphones with closed back design and gimbal head strap are some of the best around at the $249 price point and will likely be a bigger seller than the more expensive Blue Mo-Fi headphones.

data.title: Roccat Kiro: Flash Review
data.description: We take a look at the new Roccat Kiro "super-dexterous" gaming mouse and offer our first impressions. The mouse offers hot-swappable side panels, and full RGB lighting, and ROCCAT has discussed the possibility of 3D-printing support post-launch.

data.title: GameCrate Hollywood: Armani Jackson (Grey's Anatomy, Cooties) joins us for some Call of Duty
data.tags: call of duty, advanced warfare, xbox, cooties, armani jackson, gamecrate, newegg, pc, console, gaming
data.description: For this episode of GameCrate Hollywood, actor Armani Jackson joins for some Call of Duty: Advanced Warfare Exo-Survival plus we talk about his new film 'Cooties,' his work on 'Grey's Anatomy,' and his upcoming film 'Nowhere Ever After.'

data.title: GameCrate Hollywood: Straight Outta Compton's Marlon Yates battles GameCrate editor in Madden NFL 15
data.tags: marlon yates, straight outta compton, nfl, madded, gamecrate, newegg, pc, console
data.description:
Straight Outta Compton's Marlon Yates challenges GameCrate editor Q. Salazar to a game of Madden NFL 15. We also talked to Yates about what it was like portraying rapper The D.O.C. in Straight Outta Compton and how it was transitioning from a modeling career into an acting career.

Our new series, GameCrate Hollywood, pits some of Hollywood's upcoming and established stars against GameCrate editors in current and classic games plus the latest about their work and upcoming projects.

data.title: E3 2015: Call of Duty: Black Ops III, Destiny: The Taken King, Guitar Hero Live at Activision
data.tags: activision, codbo3, call of duty, black ops, guitar hero, e3, electronics expo, gaming, pc, console, xbox, playstation, destiny, newegg, gamecrate, computer
data.description: GameCrate editor Q. Salazar visits the Activision booth at E3 2015 and talks playing Call of Duty: Black Ops III, Destiny's expansion The Taken King, and Guitar Hero Live. He also apologizes for pronouncing "melee" like "meh-lee" instead of "may-lay."

data.title: E3 2015: Star Wars Battlefront feels like Battlefield
data.tags: starwars, battlefront, e3, gaming, pc, tech, newegg, gamecrate, darth vader
data.description: GameCrate editor Q. Salazar reports on his hands-on experience with EA's Star Wars Battlefront.

data.title: Virtuix Omni interview on virtual reality gaming with a treadmill
data.tags: virtual reality, omni, virtuix, gamecrate, newegg, gaming, pc, console
data.description: GameCrate editor Q. Salazar interviews Virtuix's Lorenzo Adams about the Omni, an omni-directional treadmill peripheral for use with virtual reality headsets and PCs.

data.title: Playing Oculus Rift's Edge of Nowhere - E3 2015
data.tags: edge of nowhere, oculus, virtual reality, gamecrate, newegg, e3, electronics expo, gaming
data.description: GameCrate editor Q. Salazar reports on the hands-on experience of playing Edge of Nowhere on the Oculus Rift at E3 2015.

data.title: Loading Human Developer Talks Making the Game, Virtual Reality Gaming
data.tags: loading human, virtual reality, vr, gaming, gamecrate, e3, electronics expo, newegg, computer,pc
data.description: GameCrate editor Q. Salazar speaks with Flavio Parenti of Untold Games at E3 2015 about the upcoming virtual reality game, Loading Human. The game will be available on Sony's Project Morpheus, Oculus Rift, and the Valve/HTC Vive headset next year when it's published by Maximum Games.

data.title: E3 2015: Playing Rainbow Six Siege and Assassin's Creed Syndicate at Ubisoft
data.tags: rainbow six siege, assasins creed syndicate, ubisoft, newegg, gamecrate, e3, computer, pc
data.description: GameCrate editor Q. Salazar reports from E3 2015 at the Ubisoft booth on playing Rainbow Six Siege in Terrohunt Mode and fighting gangs Assassin's Creed Syndicate.

data.title: E3 2015: Checking out XCOM 2 and Battleborn at 2K Games
data.tags: xcom, battleborn, 2k games, gamecrate, newegg, e3, computer, pc, console, xbox, playstation
data.description: Reporting from E3 2015, here's GameCrate.com's Nick discussing the XCOM 2 presentation and going hands-on with Battleborn.

data.title: Grey Goo Tips for Beginners
data.tags: grey goo, gaming, pc, newegg, gamecrate, how to, tips for beginners
data.description: Real-time strategy games can have a pretty steep learning curve. Often, you have to focus on multiple things at once like defending your base, managing your economy, and coordinating attacks. Grey Goo is no exception, which is why we made the following video going over the basics of getting started with the latest RTS game to hit the shelves.

data.title: Let's Play: Skylanders: Trap Team
data.description: NewEgg TV's Jenny and GameCrate editor Quibian "Q" Salazar-Moreno play Skylanders: Trap Team, the latest title in the Skylander series. Skylanders Trap Team introduces new characters called Trap Masters that wield powerful Traptanium weapons used to defeat Skylands’ most notorious villains including Kaos, as well as brand new Core Skylanders characters and reposed fan-favourite Skylanders characters. The game also features a variety of elementally aligned Traps with unique and interesting designs.
